OL,6,FUK inflation has remained at 8.7 per
OL,7,Fcent, latest figures show, despite
OL,8,Fhopes that the cost of goods and
OL,9,Fservices would fall in May.
OL,11,FLatest figures released by the Office
OL,12,Ffor National Statistics on Wednesday
OL,13,Fshow the Consumer Prices Index (CPI)
OL,14,Fwas 8.7 per cent in May ` higher than
OL,15,Fwhat experts had predicted.
OL,17,FEconomists believed CPI would fall to
OL,18,F8.4 per cent in May, however the
OL,19,Ffigure has remained the same as it
OL,20,Fwas in April, showing inflation
OL,21,Fremains stubbornly high in the UK.
